# Coding Rules

- TypeScript strict — no `any`
- Server Components by default — `'use client'` only when `useState` / `useEffect` is required
- Dynamic routes: `await params` (Next.js 14+)
- Tracking via `/api/track` must never block page render (fire-and-forget / background)
- Env vars only via `lib/env.ts` (validated at startup)
- No placeholder stubs — implement fully or omit
- Use pnpm for installs (`pnpm add <package>`); before adding a package, run `pnpm list <package>` to confirm it is installed

## Naming

- Tables: snake_case (`profiles`, `landing_pages`, `visits`, `leads`, `payout_periods`)
- Types: PascalCase (`Profile`, `Landing`, `Visit`, `Lead`)
- API routes: kebab-case (`/api/track/pageview`, `/api/leads/submit`)
- Components: PascalCase files under `/components/`

## Security

- Never expose Bitrix webhook URL or Supabase `service_role` in client code
- Store IP as SHA-256 hash, never raw
- Bitrix webhook endpoints must verify shared secret
- Lead form submissions: rate-limit max 3/minute per IP

## Agent Behavior

- Prefer targeted edits; for files over ~300 lines, use search/replace-style changes, not full rewrites
- If unsure about schema, check `lib/supabase/types.ts`
- If unsure about Bitrix, check `lib/bitrix/client.ts`
